<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Trains Bosnian Army Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Military Academy
started a six-month military training course for a group of
Bosnian cadets today, an official handout said.
</P>
<P>
The 21-member Bosnian team, which included 20 cadets and an
interpreter, joined the academy last Friday and the Bangladesh
army will bear the entire cost of their training including
expenditures on their food, accommodation and training fee.
</P>
<P>
After completion of their training course, the Bosnian cadets
will be commissioned officers in the Bosnian Army, the handout
added.  
</P>
