<HEADLINE> Timothy Fok Elected HK Football Association President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Timothy Fok was elected to
replace his father Henry Fok Ying Tung as president of the Hong
Kong Football Association (HKFA) here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Timothy Fok, former vice-president of the association, was
elected by a unanimous vote at HKFA's annual general meeting.
</P>
<P>
Fok Ying Tung, who has been HKFA's president for the past 27
years, said earlier this month that he would no longer take any
post in local sports organizations.
</P>
<P>
He had decided to quit from the local sports circles so as to
let himself concentrate on some major projects in the Chinese
mainland in which he has invested, he had said.
</P>
<P>
Timothy Fok has been involved in local sports for some 15
years, taking such posts as its vice-president, vice-chairman and
member of the executive board.
</P>
<P>
HKFA Chairman Hui Chun Fui was re-elected for the post.
</P>
<P>
Vice-presidents of the HKFA elected Sunday were Lam Kim Ming,
Veronica Chan, Hung Chao Hong and Wai Kee Shun.  
</P>
</TEXT>
