<HEADLINE> S. African Muslims March in Front of Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of angry Muslims
protested over the weekend in front of the Israeli embassy in
Cape Town, the legislative capital of South Africa over what they
termed the "global onslaught against Islam".
</P>
<P>
The protesters were also protesting over the depiction on
posters of the Prophet Mohammed as a pig in the West Bank town of
Hebron recently, local daily "City Press" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Outside the embassy, they chanted "Death to Israel" and "One
Zionist, one bullet".
</P>
<P>
The crowd also rocked a police vehicle and tried to remove
razor wire surrounding the embassy, local police spokesman Shane
Van Tonder said.
</P>
<P>
However, no clashes between police and demonstrators were
reported. 
</P>
