<HEADLINE> China, Indonesia Share Gold Medals in Malaysian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Indonesia showed
their strength by sharing all the gold medals of the Malaysian
Open Badminton Championship which ended in Kota Kinabalu, Sabah,
East Malaysia, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia snatched three gold titles while China captured two.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's Hermawan Susanto emerged men's singles champion
after beating Peter Gade Christensen of Denmark in 15-11, 15-11 in
45 minutes, according to reports from Kota Kinabalu.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia also clinched the men's doubles title through top
seeded and two-time champions Rexy Manaiky-Ricky Subagia who
outclassed compatriot Ariantho Antonius and Denny kantono in
straight sets 17-15, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian star Susi Susanti, who put up a dismal
performance in the recent World Championships in Glassgow, vented
her frustration by outplaying the world champion Ye Zhaoying of
China 11-5, 11-7 to clinch the women's singles title for the
fourth time.
</P>
<P>
The women's doubles crown went to China's world champions Ge
Fei and Gu Jun after disposing of their second pair of Liu Lu and
Qiang Hong 15-7,15-1.
</P>
<P>
Earlier yesterday, China's Liu Yong and Ge Fei beat Jens
Eriksen and Mariene Thomson of Denmark 15-12, 15-12 to win the
mixed doubles title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
