<HEADLINE> Helicopter Crash Kills Young Boy in Scotland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A nine-year old boy has been killed
after a helicopter giving special needs children free rides
crashed during a charity event in Scotland this afternoon,
according to a BBC television report.
</P>
<P>
Three more children and two adults were injured but they were
all under stable conditions, the report said. The helicopter came
down just a mile from the Queen Mother's official residence in
Tayside Region, Scotland.
</P>
<P>
