<HEADLINE> Drought-Stricken Algerian Farmers to Be Helped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Algerian government has
appointed a committee to compensate farmers affected by drought
and help them tide over present difficulties, it was announced
here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries said the committee
will work closely with the Algerian Bank for Rural Development,
professional associations and syndicates to prepare ground rules
for financing peasants during next cultivation seasons.
</P>
<P>
The severe drought has hit about 65 percent of the cultivated
land in Algeria, inflicting heavy losses to some 800,000 farmers
and 3.5 million hectares of cereals.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said it has been prompted to make three decisions
- regulate barley in order to protect cattle feed in pastoral
areas, support uninsured farmers to secure loans next year, and
call upon insurance companies to give compensation to farmers.
</P>
