between French and South African companies during the show and no
fewer than 450 local companies participated in the discussions,
with topics ranging from transport to medicine and packaging,
according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
During the show several French companies received South
African Bureau of Standards certificates for their products, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The transfer of technological skills and know-how from France
could turn out to be the most significant benefit resulting from
French technologies, Bouteiller noted.
</P>
<P>
French Commission for International Commercial Events Deputy
General Manager Alain Dantou said about 12,000 South African
business people visited the five-day show. 
