<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Five flood-damaged railway lines
running through east China's Zhejiang Province have resumed
operation after a round-the-clock race to repair them.
</P>
<P>
The local railway bureau has sent a great number of laborers
and materials to flood-stricken areas for the repair work on
damaged sections of the railway lines.
</P>
<P>
The massive effort of the work teams has allowed the busy
railway lines to return to normal.
</P>
<P>
Some 33 sections of the five railway lines that traverse the
province suffered landslide damage or were covered for two days by
floodwaters because of heavy rains in last week. 
