<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Voices Support to Lebanon, Palestine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today once again voiced support to the Palestinian
and Lebanese people in their struggle against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said "helping to resolve the problems of the
countries being on the forefront of struggle against the Zionist
regime is the duty of all Islamic countries and Iran is ready to
fulfill its task more vehemently than ever before."
</P>
<P>
He stressed Iran's commitment to Islamic and humane principles
and declared "Tehran supports the legitimate rights of the
Palestinian people and the stands of Lebanon vis-a-vis usurpers".
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Fuad Siniora, the special envoy of the
Lebanese president, the 64-year-old president said "Tehran-Beirut
ties will enter a new stage through exchange of political
missions.
</P>
<P>
However, Rafsanjani expressed regret over the problems which
have been imposed on the Lebanese and Palestinian peoples due
to the expansionist policies of Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The Iranian nation and government are interested in the
destiny of the Palestinian and Lebanese peoples and it is
painful to them to witness parts of Lebanon being kept under
occupation contrary to all international laws," Rafsanjani was
quoted by the official news agency IRNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani also welcomed expansion of Tehran-Beirut cooperation
in political, cultural, economic, industrial and trade fields.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Siniora conveyed the verbal message of
Lebanese President Elias Hrawi in which the latter on behalf of
the government and nation of Lebanon thanked Iran for its logical
and principled stands on condemning the aggressive policies of
the Israeli regime and for supporting the Palestinian and
Lebanese peoples.
</P>
<P>
Hrawi said in the message that Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik
Hariri is to visit Tehran to further consult with Iranian
officials and bolster Tehran-Beirut ties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, A high-ranking Lebanese economic and commercial
delegation led by Lebanese Minister of Economy and Trade Yasin
Jabir and Minister of State for Financial Affairs Fuad Siniora
has been visiting Tehran since July 12.
</P>
<P>
The local report said that the Lebanese ministers are to
meet with Iranian officials to explore ways of expanding
Tehran-Beirut economic ties and to sign two agreements on joint
ventures and exemption from customs duties. 
