<HEADLINE> Morocco Takes Medal Lead in Arab Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Morocco surged ahead in the medals
race at the eighth Pan Arab Games in Lebanon with a tally of two
golds and two bronzes.
</P>
<P>
Yunes Modrek set a games record in the long jump on Sunday
with a leap of 8.11 meters while Mustapha Bamuh snapped up
Morocco's second gold, winning the 10,000 meters in 29 minutes
22.69 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Algerian Dalila Mayyal, a 34-year-old mother of three who
failed to get selected for last month's Mediterranean Games in
Italy, won the first gold medal of the games, with a victory in
the half-marathon.
</P>
<P>
Tunisian al-Taher Mansuri won the men's marathon, retaining the
gold medal he won at the previous Pan Arab Games in Damascus in
1992.
</P>
<P>
In the shot put, Qatari Bilal Saad won gold with a 18.97 meter
heave and Nada Kawar captured the first gold medal for Jordan in
the discus.
</P>
<P>
In the football competition, Lebanon and Jordan drew 1-1 while
Kuwait defeated Mauritania 3-1.
</P>
<P>
In volleyball, Algeria defeated title-holder Bahrain 3-1 and
Egypt downed Qatar by the same margin while Saudi Arabia and
Lebanon scored 3-0 victories over Kuwait and Libya, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The games formally opened on Saturday and run to July 27.
</P>
