<HEADLINE> Cholera Breaks out in Nepali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Continued rains and polluted
water have caused a cholera outbreak in this capital city of Nepal
these days, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Cholera germs have been found in 15 to 16 patients affected by
gastro-enteritis recently, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Hospital sources said 34 out of the 472 patients of
gastro-enteritis have shown symptoms of cholera till last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
As the monsoon will linger until early September, cholera is
expected to spread further.  
</P>
