<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Tamil Maanila Congress
(TMC), a party in the Indian coalition government, said today that
the announcement by the regional party Davida Munnetra Kazhagam
(DMK) to withdraw from the United Front (UF) government would have
serious consequences.
</P>
<P>
"It is another crisis for the UF, which is already facing a
crisis due to Bihar Chief Minister Laloo Prasad Yadav's coming out
of the Janata Dal, the major constituent of the UF, and forming
Rashtriya Janata Dal on July 5," TMC President G.K. Moopanar told
reporters at TMC headquarters in Chennai, capital of Tamil Nadu.
</P>
<P>
