Chennai, also headquarters of the DMK, that his party would
withdraw its ministers from the UF government but to support it
from outside.
</P>
<P>
K. Karunanidhi said his party is being used by some UF members
"as a channel to settle their personal scores."
</P>
<P>
"It is a serious matter as Mr. Karunanidhi is one of the
founding fathers of the UF. This will certainly have its impact on
the UF government," Moopanar added.
</P>
<P>
Since the split of the Janata Dal, UF members have been widely
divided over whether to allow the newly formed Rashtriya Janata
Dal to enter the UF, a coalition formed last year comprising 13
regional parties.
</P>
<P>
While the DMK expressed support for Rashtriya Janata Dal's
entry, some other UF members have been strongly against it.
</P>
