<HEADLINE> Credit Card Cheat Caught in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A man using his credit card to
get a large number of goods by making an overdraft was caught
today in the capital of east China's Zhejiang province.
</P>
<P>
The man, whose name was Li, had used four credit cards from
different banks in the city since 1993 to buy 300,000 yuan worth
of goods by overdrawing from his credit accounts. To avoid
prosecution he hid in various locations.
</P>
<P>
The police of Hangzhou finally arrested him for violations of
finance laws. It was the first case in the city.
</P>
<P>
One study has shown that 812 people in the city have overdrawn
a total of nine million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local police are giving a hand to the local banks and have
informed the credit card cheats that they must pay for the
overdrafts within a certain period of time or face punishment.
</P>
</TEXT>
