<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets With German Social Democratic Party Reps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, Chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said here
today that the leaders of China and Germany should view bilateral
ties from a strategic perspective to secure a healthy and stable
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who also is a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), made the remarks while meeting with Herta
Daeubler-Gmelin, vice-chairman of Germany's Social Democratic
Party (SDP), and her party.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qiao noted that more Germans visiting China
could help increase mutual understanding and promote bilateral
relations, and that long-term friendly and co-operative
relationship between the two big countries would not only serve
the fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also peace and
stability in the world.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chairman also briefed the German visitors on the
people's congress system in China and the NPC's operation in the
construction of democracy and legal system in the past few
years. China puts much importance to promoting democracy and legal
system in accordance with the actual conditions in the country,
while developing its economy, Qiao told the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Gmelin told Qiao that German statesmen place importance on
reinforcing Germany's relations with China. Her current China
visit is aimed at boosting the links between the SDP and CPC, she
said, adding that the exchange between the two parties would
increase mutual understanding and promote bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Gmelin and her party are here on a good-will visit to China as
guests of the CPC. Li Shuzheng, head of the International
Department of the CPC Central Committee held working talks last
Friday with Gmelin. The German visitors are also scheduled to tour
Chengdu, Lhasa and Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
