<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Edges Lithuania 3-2 in Davis Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Egypt defeated Lithuania 3-2 in a
group 2 tie of Euro-African zone of the Davis Cup tournament on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Egypt clinched the victory with a singles match in which Hisham
Humeideh outlasted Lithuania's Evaenidos Cariovas 6-2, 7-6 (7-4),
6-7 (5-7), 5-7, 2-3 (11-9).
</P>
<P>
The match was resumed on Monday after being suspended by
darkness on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The teams were tied at 2-2 on Sunday when play was halted. At
that point, Cariovas was leading Humeideh 3-2 in the fifth set.
</P>
<P>
Under Davis Cup rules, Humeideh and Cariovas were required to
play Monday until one beat the other by two points. The half-hour
game ended with Humeideh outscoring Cariovas 11-9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
