<HEADLINE> Pak PM to Visit US: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif will pay an official visit to the United States by the end
of September this year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan told the media here today that
"the exact date of the visit will be announced shortly."
</P>
<P>
Replying to questions, he said, "all matters of common interest
of bilateral and regional nature would come under discussion
during the meeting."
</P>
<P>
He said that the forthcoming visit is "the success of the
government's foreign policy."  
</P>
