<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gebrselassie to Miss Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's 10,000 meters world
record holder Haile Gebrselassie announced here on Monday he would
not participate in the coming world athletics championships.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic 10,000 meters gold medalist said the reason behind
his decision was because the track for the Athens event next month
was too hard.
</P>
<P>
He said he had suffered great injuries at the Atlanta Olympics
with blood flowing from his soles and it took him a long time to
recover from that injury.
</P>
<P>
"I do not want to undergo similar sufferings," he added.
</P>
<P>
Gebrselassie said he decided to pull out after hearing the
Athens track was similar to the one used at the Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
He broke the world 10,000 meters record with a time of 26
minutes 31.32 seconds at the Bislett Games grand prix in Oslo,
Norway, on July 4 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
