<HEADLINE> Mandela Arrives in Jakarta to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- South African President Nelson
Mandela arrived here today for a three-day visit to Indonesia in
an effort to promote cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Mandela flew to the capital city of Jakarta from Indonesia's
island resort Bali, where he arrived last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The South African leader is scheduled to attend a state banquet
this evening at the State Palace.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday morning, Mandela and Indonesian President Soeharto
will have talks, after which the two leaders will witness the
signing of an agreement on avoiding double taxation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Mandela's visit, his first since assuming office in 1994, aims
to boost cooperation and already good relations between the two
countries, officials here said.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries was valued at about 200 million
U.S. dollars in 1996, when Indonesia exported 107 million dollars
worth of goods to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Mandela will fly to Bangkok on Wednesday to pay a two-day visit
to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In March, Mandela visited the Philippines, Brunei, Singapore
and Malaysia as part of South Africa's drive to increase trade and
investment links with Southeast Asian countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
