<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Police Cop It in Crime Crackdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 2,125 police officers in
Bulgaria have been disciplined so far this year for breaking
regulations and 111 have been sacked, the Bulgarian media reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The capital Sofia had the highest number of police violations,
with 88 officers disciplined, the media quoted the interior
ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The most common offenses were excessive use of force, brutality
and accidental homicide, bribery, abuse of power, theft and losing
handguns.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian police have taken action to curb corruption and
discipline violations within the police force as part of a
nationwide crackdown on crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
