<HEADLINE> Malaysian Supreme Head of State Visits Suzhou, Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Supreme Head of State of Malaysia
Tuanku Ja'afar and his entourage today visited Suzhou, a booming
city in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Ja'afar, accompanied by Chen Minzhang, chairman of the Chinese
government reception committee and Minister of Health, visited a
well-known park, an embroidery research institute and a
state-level new and high-tech development zone in the city, which
is famous for its fine gardens and embroidery articles.
</P>
<P>
Vice-governor Wang Rongbing of Jiangsu, met with Ja'afar and
briefed him on the economic progress in the city and his province
as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Ja'afar said that he is glad to be here in China to see its
achievements, and expressed his hope for further bilateral
cooperation in various fields in the future.
</P>
<P>
On July 13, vice-mayor Chen Liangyu of Shanghai, China's
largest financial center, met with Ja'afar on behalf of mayor Xu
Kuangdi. Both had a cordial exchange of views and expressed the
hope for closer cooperation in economic and other fields.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that in 1996, the trade volume between Shanghai
and Malaysia reached 201 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ja'afar arrived in Shanghai Sunday afternoon from Hangzhou,
capital of neighboring Zhejiang Province. 
</P>
