<HEADLINE> Elephants Destroy Crops in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A herd of elephants last
week invaded several villages in Rombo District, destroying crops
and causing panic among the residents, local paper "Guardian"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Rombo District Commissioner (DC), Peniel Ole Saitabau was
quoted as saying that the elephants migrated into the district
from the neighboring Tsavo National Park of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Saitabau said that the elephants moved in at night and it was
very difficult to trace them.
</P>
<P>
He said that some rangers and
villagers in the affected villages are now guarding their
property to avoid destruction by the tuskers.
</P>
<P>
There has been a migration of elephants in recent years
because an open corridor which used to separate Tanzania's Rombo
District and Kenya's Longido District has been invaded by
developers, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
