<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Index Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A big surge on the first trading
day of this week pushed the Hong Kong stocks up to a record high
close.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index, the key indicator of 33 blue chips listed
on the Hong Kong bourse, picked up 145.65 points or 0.96 percent
today to close at a new high of 15,370.94 points.
</P>
<P>
Strong gaining momentum swept the Hong Kong stock market late
last week, creating a record high close of 15,225.29 points on
Friday with healthy turnover of 18.5 billion HK dollars (2.4
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Total turnover today rose to about 19 billion HK dollars (2.45
billion U.S. dollars). Utilities and finance stocks took the lead
to go up 334 points and 251 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said that earlier gloomy forecast on the
properties market was reversed as private developers volunteered
to cut housing prices before the government would take any
regulatory measure.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the currency chaos plaguing some Southeastern Asian
countries could bring more money into Hong Kong. After a short
period of correction, China-affiliated corporations, known as the
red chips, regained its momentum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
