<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Exports Drop in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
re-exports in May 1997 was 100.2 billion HK dollars (12.85 billion
U.S. dollars), down marginally by 0.1 percent compared with the
same month last year, while that of domestic exports fell 4.5
percent to 16.8 billion HK dollars (2.15 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Imports in the month increased 3.5 percent to 134.5 billion HK
dollars (17.24 billion U.S. dollars), according to official
statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, the value of re-exports
totaled 474 billion HK dollars (60.77 billion U.S. dollars),
increasing 3.3 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of imports in the first five months of this year
totaled 635.8 billion HK dollars (81.51 billion U.S. dollars), up
4.2 percent from the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
