<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leaving Chinese Chief of Sino-Portuguese JLG Urges Quicker Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Guo Jiading, who is leaving the post
as chief representative of the Chinese side of the Sino-Portuguese
Joint Liaison Group (JLG) very soon, said here today that the
transitional process in Macao should be quickened.
</P>
<P>
"Time is urgent but the task is arduous," he told about 400
guests attending a reception on his leaving today. "The JLG should
pick up speed in the handling of the localization of the civil
service, the localization of law and the use of Chinese as an
official language, as well as the transfer of archives and
government assets."
</P>
<P>
The 66-year-old ambassador is retiring, leaving the post to Han
Zhaokang, who co-headed several working panels of the JLG. Han is
expected to come from Beijing at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
Guo said that both China and Portugal should start from a
strategic point of view and make greater efforts in handling
transitional issues.
</P>
<P>
The second chief representative of the Chinese side of the JLG,
Guo came to Macao in April 1993. He said he felt "proud" as the
JLG reached consensus on a wide range of issues over the past four
years.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal reached agreement on the establishment and
operation of the Macao International Airport, which was
inaugurated in November 1995. They also agreed on the note-issuing
by the Bank of China Macao Branch in the same year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, two of the five leading laws in Macao -- the
criminal code and the code of criminal procedure -- have been
localized after being reviewed by the JLG.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also signed agreements not long ago on the
handling of the Orient Foundation, which is accused by local
people as siphoning money from Macao to Lisbon, on the revision of
the casino contract and the establishment of a new foundation,
all of which had haunted the JLG for years.
</P>
<P>
"These fruits represent the friendly cooperation between China
and Portugal on the basis of the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration," the ambassador said. "They have laid favorable
conditions for future work of the JLG."
</P>
<P>
Guo was Chinese ambassador to Portugal before he became the
chief representative of the Chinese side of the JLG. He was bid
farewell today by officials of the Macao Government, Xinhua News
Agency Macao Branch, top executives of Chinese firms in Macao, and
other local celebrities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970714.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan to Fight Population Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan will take measures to
fight a crisis of slowing population growth and shortening life
span, said a report released at a population conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The average life span of the Kazakh people decreased by 4.7
years to 64.9 in 1995 from 1990, and the natural population growth
rate dropped to 5.3 persons per thousand in 1996 from 13 persons
per thousand in 1991, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the birth giving rate of women was declining while
the infant mortality rate increased. The education level of
children also went down, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the government and non-governmental organizations
attributed the current situation to the slow development of the
country's economy, deteriorating environment and poor education
and health conditions.
</P>
<P>
The conference urged government institutions and
non-governmental organizations to promote economic development and
establish a new social security system, so as to solve the
nation's population crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
