<HEADLINE> Cricket Asia Cup Starts in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Asia Cup Cricket
tournament started in Sri Lanka on Monday when world champions Sri
Lanka meet Pakistan in the opening match of the four nation
contest.
</P>
<P>
The other two participating countries India and Bangladesh will
clash with each other on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Cup has been held on five previous occasions, the
first being in 1984, with India winning four, and Sri Lanka
triumphing in 1986 when it was held here.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka took this year's Aka I Cup in Sharjah in April and
followed it up by winning the Independence Cup in India in May
beating Pakistan in the finals on both events. 
