<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets With Chad Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met with a
delegation from Patriotic Movement of Salvation (PMS) of Chad here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by PMS chairman Maldom Bada Abbas, is
here on a good-will visit to China at the invitation of the
Communist Party of China (CPC)
</P>
<P>
Qiao, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said that the CPC is pleased
with the smooth development of its friendly and cooperative ties
with PMS since the two established relations in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The CPC, the Chinese government and the Chinese people have
been working hard to reinforce their relations and cooperation
with African countries, Qiao said, adding that the current China
tour by chairman Maldom would enhance the mutual understanding and
friendship between the two parties and the two peoples and promote
the development of the friendly ties of cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chairman expressed his appreciation of and thanks for
the adherence to the "one China" position and the support to the
peaceful reunification of China by the PMS and the Chad government.
</P>
<P>
Maldom said that PMS and the Chad government congratulate China
on the return of Hong Kong to the motherland and hope that the
reunification of China would be realized at an early date.
</P>
<P>
He said China has achieved remarkable progress in its economic
growth and has accumulated a lot of experience. Chad hopes to
become better acquainted with these experience through visits and
exchanges, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li Shuzheng, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, held working talks with the delegation last
Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
