<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall to New Low on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell another 12.54 points to close at 1954.6
today, marking a new low level in at least three years.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 114.58 million units, valued at
286.85 million Singapore dollars (about 200.59 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 244 to 76, while 308
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Kuala Lumpur Industry was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 19.41 million units. It was followed by
Mulpha Resources which had 8.92 million shares traded. Hong Kong
Land was next with 4.63 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sembawang led the gainers of the day as it rose 50 cents
to finish at 24.2 Singapore dollars. GE Life and Gentings
increased 40 cents each to end at 16.5 and 6.85 Singapore dollars
respectively. Rurwill closed 34 cents higher at 1.46 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, H Royal was the biggest loser as it declined
1.44 dollars to end at 2.4 dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) Foreign fell 70 cents to close at 27.7 Singapore dollars,
while NBT finished 50 cents lower at 20.9 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
