<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Kidnappers Killed by Police in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine police today killed
six members of a notorious kidnap-for-ransom gang in a gun battle
in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Efren Fernandez, director of the Criminal Investigation Group
of the Philippine National Police, said that the operation against
the gang has been going on for three months.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez said after an informer tipped off his office that the
gang would conduct another kidnapping operation, he sent two teams
to the reported area.
</P>
<P>
But the policemen in an unmarked car were fired upon by the
members of the gang, prompting them to return fire. After the
crossfire, the police found some handguns on the scene.
</P>
<P>
The gang was responsible for the kidnapping of two
Chinese-Filipino businessmen, a carnapping and some robberies,
police said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a total of 81 people have been taken
hostage in the country in the first half of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
