<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Guards N. Korean Ship Despite Rebel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A boat of the Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) which tried to intercept a Sri Lankan Navy
patrol boat guarding North Korean Morang Bong ship was destroyed
by the Navy, killing six rebels on board and damaging another boat
last night.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, the Navy had observed four
LTTE boats in the area where Morang Bong is anchored off
Mullaitivu coast.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels are trying their best to guard the ship from
being taken over by the Navy, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The vessel, hired by Sri Lanka to transport goods to the Jaffna
Peninsula, was on its way to Colombo last Tuesday when it was
abducted at Mullaitivu, more than 200 km north of the destination.
</P>
<P>
The Korean crew was released by the LTTE last Saturday through
the International Committee of the Red Cross, but the LTTE has
not indicated whether to release the ship so far, the reports
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
