<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Province Tries to Find More Storage Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Jiangxi Province, one of China's
leading rice-growing areas, will face not only a record harvest
of summer grain but also the problem of what to do with an excess
supply.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi Province lacks storage capacity for 2.5 billion
kilograms. In response, the province's Governor Shu Shengyou has
urged all counties to build additional grain depots.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has already put aside 40 million yuan
(4.82 million US dollars) for makeshift storehouse construction,
according to officials.
</P>
<P>
They said the storage capacity will meet all necessary
requirements before this summer harvest.
</P>
<P>
Among the 8.5 billion kilograms of in-stock rice, early rice
accounts for about seven billion kilograms, including that which
has been in storage for four years.
</P>
<P>
Traditional early rice is not appealing to rice consumers who
don't like the taste.
</P>
<P>
"To basically solve the problem of overstock, we must readjust
the mix of farm produce," Shu said.
</P>
<P>
He said farmers should be permitted to plant whatever
they like as long as they don't destroy high-yield areas needed
for tree planting or fish breeding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970714.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Headway in Sustained Development Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China is making progress in
carrying out its sustainable development strategy in 14 major
social and economic areas, according to a recent government report.
</P>
<P>
The report Chinese Government presented to the UN Conference on
Environment and Development shows that the natural growth of
China's population in 1995 dropped 3.84 per thousand,
compared with the figure five years earlier.
</P>
<P>
The drop indicate that China's birth rate is apparently lower
than the average birth rate of other developing countries, and
the excessive birth increase has been brought under control.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the Chinese people are beginning to have
better educational opportunities.
</P>
<P>
China has placed special emphasis on development-oriented
poverty relief in a move to enhance poor people's ability to help
themselves. As a result, its poor population has dropped from 80
million in 1993 to 58 million in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It has also increased efforts to improve the living environment
and residential conditions.
</P>
<P>
Varied achievements have been scored in the agriculture and
rural economy, industry, energy and consumer goods production,
land resources, forest resources, water resources, marine
resources, disaster prevention and reduction, atmosphere
protection, solid waste disposal, and biological diversification
protection, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
