<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia's Copper Output Rises in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Consolidated Copper
Mines (ZCCM) yielded 25,422 tons of finished copper products in
May, the second month of the 1997/98 financial year.
</P>
<P>
The May figure was 322 tons above target and over 4,000 tons
better than the previous month's which stood at 21,380 tons,
according to the latest issue of the Mining Mirror, organ of the
state-owned copper conglomerate ZCCM.
</P>
<P>
The output increase was attributed to the good performance of
the smelters in three of the company's divisions -- Mufulira,
Luanshya and Nchanga -- following the resolution of the heavy
fuel oil problems the company previously experienced.
</P>
<P>
However, the company produced only 301 tons of cobalt in May,
76 tons below the estimated target.
</P>
<P>
The ZCCM is the major foreign exchange earner of Zambia whose
over 80 percent foreign exchange is from the export of copper
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
