<HEADLINE> Experts Discuss Sustained Development of Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 80 experts from both
sides of the Taiwan Straits have attended a seminar in Guangzhou
on the development of agricultural science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The seminar provided an opportunity for experts to hold
in-depth discussions on sustainable development of agriculture,
livestock breeding techniques, agricultural engineering, and food
processing.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the seminar, Lu Zhonghe,
vice-governor of economically-booming Guangdong Province, said
that his province and Taiwan share similar natural conditions
and have potential for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong now has 9,000 agricultural technique research
institutes employing a total of 20,000 researchers, he said,
adding that science and technology contribute 40 percent to
Guangdong's increased agricultural production annually.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, researchers on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits have frequently worked together on ag-science projects.
</P>
<P>
Business people from Taiwan are showing a great interest in
investing in various kinds of agricultural enterprises in the
southeast coastal areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
