<DOCNO> XIE19970714.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Lifter Claims Last World Record at Asian Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Wang Yanmei of China claimed the
last world record on the final day of the 10th women's and 19th
men's Asian weightlifting championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Wang snatched 112.5 kilograms to beat the previous world mark
of 109 kg held by compatriot Ding Meiyuan.
</P>
<P>
Wang then skipped her third and final attempt in snatch to save
energy for the clean and jerk events.
</P>
<P>
But she was eventually beaten in the jerk event by Chen
Hsiao-Lien of Chinese Taipei who lifted 140kg. Wang also lifted
140kg but she had to settle for the second place.
</P>
<P>
Wang managed to win the overall gold with a total of
252.5kg. Chen finished second with 250kg.
</P>
<P>
The women's 83kg category was dominated by Zhang Xiaoli of
China. She took the category's three golds, but her winning
results were quite modest compared with the world records.
</P>
<P>
In the men's section, Cui Wenhua of China met no challenge from
his opponents.
</P>
<P>
Cui took the snatch gold with 185kg, beating his solo opponent
Hironobo Asada of Japan by 35 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The clean and jerk gold medal also went to Cui after he lifted
200kg in his second attempt. That also gave him a winning total of
385 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The men's over-108kg class was won by Khalilovi of Uzbekistan
who snatched 17kg, jerked 210kg and garnered a 380kg total for a
clean sweep. 
</P>
</TEXT>
