<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
eased today in good trading volume for a Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 11 points lower at 2,505 with a turnover
of 89 million NZ dollars (59 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the falls, down 5 cents to 779 cents, as
higher interest rates hit yield-sensitive stocks.
</P>
<P>
Most other leaders all fell. Air New Zealand dropped 2c to
319c. Fletcher Paper slipped 6c to 341c. Brierley Investment eased
2c to 137c. Carter Holt Harvey dipped 1c to 341c.
</P>
<P>
Lion Nathan was the only leader holding its ground, steady at
388c.
</P>
<P>
The smaller companies index jumped, partly on hopes that a
lower kiwi dollar will help exporters.
</P>
<P>
There were 48 rises and 45 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
