<HEADLINE> PLA Chief of General Staff Meets Thai Air Commander-in-Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of general staff
of the People's Liberation Army of China met here today with Amorn
Naewmalee, Thai air commander-in-chief.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to Naewmalee, Fu said that China and Thailand
are friendly neighbors whose people and armed forces have enjoyed
traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation of the two sides in political, economic and
cultural fields has continued to grow since they forged diplomatic
relations more than 20 years ago, Fu said.
</P>
<P>
There are frequent contacts between the senior leaders of the
two sides, including those of the two armed forces, Fu said,
adding that this has played an important role in increasing the
friendship of the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu noted that the armed forces of the two countries also learn
from each other's experiences, and work together to build their
military systems and provide the support of the military in the
national economic construction.
</P>
<P>
Fu said he believes that Naewmalee's visit will play a positive
role in expanding the contacts and cooperation between the two
militaries.
</P>
<P>
Naewmalee said that the People's Liberation Army is a great
military force, and that its quality and role in national politics
and economic construction has become the focus of world attention.
</P>
<P>
The Thai armed forces hope to strengthen exchanges and
cooperation with the PLA in areas of personnel training and
technical equipment, Naewmalee added.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shunyao, PLA commander of the air force, also attended the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
