<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Rebels Step up Attacks in East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have stepped up attacks in
the East of the island country.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here today, the rebels mounted
twin
attacks Sunday, killing a policeman and a civilian and wounding
four police constables at Ampara, and wounding four police
constables and wounding a home guard and three civilians at
Valachenai in the same district.
</P>
<P>
At the Ampara check point, the rebels had removed a radio
transmitter and had set fire to the check point, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the incident, Sri Lanka's airforce had bombed
the area where the rebels were reported to have gathered. Several
rebel cadres are believed to be killed in the confrontations and
during the bombing.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war for a
separate state in the North and East of Sri Lanka since 1983.
</P>
