<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The meeting of the Nepal-India
Joint Working Group on Border Management is to be held here on
July 16, a Nepali newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting will work out ways to curb border
crossing between the two countries by undesirable elements and to
regulate movements across the border, the national Kathmandu Post
reported quoting a government source.
</P>
