<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Mayor Attacked for Duty Negligence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Ivo Kosatik, major of the Czech
city Olomouc, has been severely attacked for neglect of duty and
ignoring his people's sufferings, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Olomouc was hit recently by heavy floods rarely seen in
history, suffering enormous economic and personal losses.
</P>
<P>
At a time when he was badly needed to lead his people to fight
the floods to tide over the disaster, Kosatik, however, went to
Greece on Friday with his family for holidays.
</P>
<P>
Kosatik has been strongly condemned after what he has done is
disclosed by the press.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus immediately said Kosatik's
behaviour is "unimaginable," while Jiri Vlach, vice-chairman of
the Chamber of Deputies, said, it "is an absurdity, which is
totally against the principles as a human being."
</P>
<P>
"He is not qualified to be our mayor as he deserted us when we
were in the most difficult moment," said an Olomouc resident,
representing locals who are considering a motion to expel Kosatik
from the ruling Civic Democratic Party, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
