<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Tourism Booming in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, and Shaanxi and Gansu provinces have made
concerted efforts to develop tourism along the Baoji-Zhongwei
Railway connecting the three areas.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 scenic spots have been developed along the 489-km
railway line from Baoji City in Shaanxi to Zhongwei City in
Ningxia. Tourists worldwide have flocked to see the natural
scenery and historical relics there, such as ancient towns and
tombs, the Taoist "holy land," sandy hills, and the culture of the
famous "Silk Road."
</P>
<P>
Experts agree that the railway has helped to form a "tourism
corridor" for the three areas.
</P>
<P>
To further promote tourism, Ningxia has planned to build ten
tourism tourism zones over the next three years, and Baoji City
has decided to invest 450 million yuan in developing four tourism
projects including the Tiantai Mountains Forest Park by the end of
the century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
