<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Parliament Chairman Highlights National Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Yugoslav Chamber
of Republics (parliament) Srdja Bozevic today underscored the
importance of unity of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
At celebrations in Podogricca, capital of Republic of
Montenegro (Crna Gora), on the 56th anniversary of military
uprising against the German Fascist aggression, Bozevic said, the
hope of people in both the Republic of Serbia and the Republic of
Montenegro to live in the same country serves as the basic policy
of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and these two republics.
</P>
<P>
The principles of coordination of common functions,
distribution of power and division of authorities specified in the
federal constitution guarantee equality of the two republics, said
Bozevic who is acting president of the nation.
</P>
<P>
In a federal state, broad prospects for Montenegro's
development and prosperity is created, not only in the interest of
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and its two republics, but also
in the interest of all citizens in the federal republic, he said.
</P>
<P>
Montenegro's position is not allowed to become an issue due to
the exclusiveness of any organization or individual, added the
chairman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
