<HEADLINE> Italy's Zanardi Wins Cleveland GP CART Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Alessandro Zanardi,
overcoming two penalties which had dropped him to 22nd place, won
the Cleveland Grand Prix CART race today.
</P>
<P>
By driving a Reynard Honda, the Italian motorist averaged
111.848 mph (179.996 kph). He took the lead with six laps
remaining and finished ahead of Brazilian Gil de Ferran in a
Reynard Honda by 1.281 seconds. American Bryan Herta was third, in
a Reynard Ford.
</P>
<P>
It was Zanardi's second win of the year and fifth of his
career.
</P>
<P>
Paul Tracy of Canada, who finished seventh in a Penske
Mercedes-Benz, continued to lead the series points standings with
106. Fellow Canadian Greg Moore was second with 95 and de Ferran
third with 94.
</P>
<P>
The series moves to Toronto on July 20 for the 11th round of
the 17-race series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
