<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Japan 5-0 in Fed Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The United States swept Japan
5-0 in the Fed Cup World Group One playoff Sunday at Brookline,
Massachusetts, the United States.
</P>
<P>
American Lindsay Davenport's 6-4 7-6 (7-1) win over Japanese Ai
Sugiyama, combined with two singles victories on Saturday, gave
the United States an insurmountable 3-0 lead in the best-of-five
competition. The Americans went on to a 5-0 victory by taking the
day's second singles match and the doubles.
</P>
<P>
The victory qualified the United States for World Group One
contention in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Americans were upset by the Netherlands 3-2 in February in
this year's championship competition.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, ranked seventh in the world, trailed 3-1 in the
first set and 4-2 in the second.
</P>
<P>
Kimberly Po beat Naoko Sawamatsu 6-2 6-4 in the last singles
and in the doubles, Davenport and Po beat Naoko Kijimuta and Nana
Miyagi 6-4 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Po, ranked 15th in the world, was a late replacement for
13th-ranked Mary Joe Fernandez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
