<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills Eight in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A single-engine plane
crashed in a densely-populated area in southeastern Brazil today,
killing at least eight people and injuring dozens, police said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred around 2 p.m. (1700 GMT) in the city of
Conselheiro Lafaiete, 96 kilometers south of Belo Horizonte, in
the state of Minas Gerais.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the cause of the crash was not yet
known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
