<HEADLINE> Zabel Wins Eighth Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Erik Zabel captured his third stage
victory in the Tour de France cycling race on Sunday after winning
a photo-finish verdict in the eighth stage from Bordeaus to Pau.
</P>
<P>
Italian Nicola Minali finished second and Dutchman Jeroen
Blijlevens came third after the quartet hit the finish line
together at the end of the 161.5-km race.
</P>
<P>
The fourth place went to Frenchman Frederic Moncassin.
</P>
<P>
The win helped Zabel cut the overall lead of Cedric Vasseur of
France to one minute and 21 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Zabel won Saturday's stage and crossed the line first on Friday
but was later disqualified and pushed back to last for pushing.
</P>
</TEXT>
