<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Thermal Springs Found in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Twelve thermal springs found in
Kangding County, southwest China's Sichuan Province, have been
recently identified as rare mineral water resources with medicinal
properties.
</P>
<P>
The springs were found by the Chengdu branch of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences at the foot of Mount Paoma in the county. They
are located in an area of about two sq km at an elevation of about
3,000 m.
</P>
<P>
The flow of mineral water from the springs, the temperature of
which is 59 degrees centigrade, exceeds 2,763 cu m a day.
</P>
<P>
A spa and tourism resort may be built around the springs,
according to local officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
