<HEADLINE> Tourism Boom in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region has made an effort to develop its tourism
industry in recent years, and the move has paid off.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.5 million Chinese tourists came to Ningxia in 1996,
bringing 250 million yuan in earnings to the local tourism
business. The region also had 4,200 foreign visitors who spent
1.14 million US dollars here.
</P>
<P>
As for the region's tourism programs, its "Sand Lake" had
400,000 tourists from all over the country and earned 10 million yuan
from visitors last year.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Tourism Bureau has developed a number of new
tourism programs this year, like sand hill, tombs of ancient
kings, stone paintings, desert exploration, visits to ethnic
minority villages, and silk road travel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
