<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multimedia Software Helping Foreigners Learn Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A multimedia software program
designed to help foreigners learn Chinese more quickly has been
developed by the Ningxia Computer Research Institute in Yinchuan,
the capital of China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The interactive software contains a video with cartoon figures,
sound, and Chinese characters that help foreigners learn to speak
and write Chinese. It also provides useful information about the
country's long history and superb landscape.
</P>
<P>
Exercises at the end of each unit help foreigners pass the HSK
Test, a TOFEL-like exam that evaluates Chinese-language ability of
non-native speakers.
</P>
<P>
A textbook that accompanies the software was edited by Huang
Zhengcheng, professor and vice-chairman of the Chinese
Language and Culture College of Beijing Language and Culture
University.
</P>
<P>
Multi-lingual compact-disc versions of the software were
released by Beijing University Press recently to meet the needs of
British, German, French, Korean, and Japanese studying Chinese.
</P>
</TEXT>
